org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen
Interface NeatParameters

All Known Implementing Classes:
SimpleNeatParameters
public interface NeatParameters

NeatParameters defines the environment and the algorithm to use for a NEAT process.

Author:
Aidan Morgan

setInnovationIdsStart

void setInnovationIdsStart(long l)
Calling this allows the starting number of the innovation id's to be reset from zero, to the provided value. It is the responsibility of the caller of this method to ensure that the provided id is not already assigned to something else inside the context of this NeatParameters.

Parameters:
l - the id to start from.
